## Spec Kit workflow (PO gates)

| Phase | Command | Output |
|-------|---------|--------|
| Specify | `/speckit-specify` | `spec.md` + `checklists/requirements.md` (Status: **Pending PO Review**) |
| PO approves spec | `/speckit-approve-spec` | Status → **Approved**; **auto-runs** `/speckit-plan` in the same turn → `plan.md` for PO review |
| PO approves plan | `/speckit-tasks` | `tasks.md` |
| Implement | `/speckit-implement` | code changes |

**When the user says the spec is approved** (e.g. "chấp thuận spec", "spec OK", "approve spec"):
1. Run the **`speckit-approve-spec`** skill immediately (read `.cursor/skills/speckit-approve-spec/SKILL.md`).
2. Do **not** stop after updating status — continue with the full **`speckit-plan`** workflow in the same session so PO receives `plan.md` to evaluate.
3. Do **not** ask the user to run `/speckit-plan` separately unless they explicitly want to regenerate an existing plan.

Optional: `/speckit-clarify` before approval if requirements are still ambiguous.
